            def longest_nodigit_same_ends(s):
                best = ""
                best_i = 0
            
                for i in range(len(s)):
                    if s[i].isdigit():
                        continue
                    for j in range(len(s) - 1, i - 1, -1):
                        if s[j].isdigit():
                            continue
                        if s[i] == s[j]:
                            sub = s[i:j + 1]
                            if any(ch.isdigit() for ch in sub):
                                continue
                            if len(sub) > len(best):
                                best = sub
                                best_i = i
                            break
            
                return best
